<paragraph id="8B8536EB5B775003FF44FF4137A35F73" blockId="6.[175,1004,194,401]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">
The specimen (SBL 
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B775003FE0DFF4037905EE6" bold="true" box="[398,416,195,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">¼</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CC29B0E5B775003FE25FF4137C25EE6" box="[422,498,194,215]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" unit="mm" value="6.8">6.8 mm</quantity>
) belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D685B775003FD11FF4134F65EE6" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1828" box="[658,710,194,215]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agilis">
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B775003FD11FF4134F65EE6" box="[658,710,194,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">agilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and is conspecific with specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D685B775003FEC2FF5E34035EC3" authority="Allen, 1972" authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="1972" box="[321,563,221,242]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B775003FEC2FF5E379D5EC3" box="[321,429,221,242]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">L. minutus</emphasis>
Allen, 1972
</taxonomicName>
[NEW SYNONYMY]. This species belongs to a subgroup of several closely related species. However, I was unable to find any structural differences between the 
<typeStatus id="548188495B775003FD86FE9134685F16" box="[517,600,274,295]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D685B775003FD02FE9134D85F16" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" box="[641,744,274,295]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B775003FD02FE9134D85F16" box="[641,744,274,295]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">L. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the 
<specimenCount id="9D3CFD625B775003FCC5FE9135FF5F16" box="[838,975,274,295]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">two paratypes</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D685B775003FF2CFEAE37255F73" authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="1972" box="[175,277,301,322]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B775003FF2CFEAE37255F73" box="[175,277,301,322]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">L. minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
I have seen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8536EB5B775003FF44FEC4346A5FA0" blockId="6.[175,1004,194,401]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">
The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D685B775003FEB9FEC437955F6D" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" box="[314,421,327,348]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B775003FEB9FEC437955F6D" box="[314,421,327,348]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">L. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was listed as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D685B775003FCAAFEC437205F46" authority="(LeConte)" baseAuthorityName="LeConte" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="velox" subSpecies="piciventris">
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B775003FCAAFEC435DC5F6D" box="[809,1004,327,348]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">L. velox piciventris</emphasis>
(LeConte)
</taxonomicName>
by Schaupp (1880:20) but the 
<typeStatus id="548188495B775003FDDBFEE1349F5F46" box="[600,687,354,375]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D685B775003FD5AFEE1356B5F46" box="[729,859,354,375]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piciventris">
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B775003FD5AFEE1356B5F46" box="[729,859,354,375]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">L. piciventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly not conspecific with the 
<typeStatus id="548188495B775003FEFAFEFF37FC5FA0" box="[377,460,380,401]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D685B775003FE6CFEFF34645FA0" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" box="[495,596,380,401]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B775003FE6CFEFF34645FA0" box="[495,596,380,401]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">L. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
